    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FB-EPD%252021-0135-02-00-00-EN%2520ETEX%2520-%2520cedral%2520-%2520signed/scenarios",
      "@type": "ScenarioSet",
      "sectionTitle": "DETAILS OF THE UNDERLYING SCENARIOS USED TO CALCULATE THE IMPACTS",
      "scenarios": [
        {
          "module": "A1",
          "number": null,
          "title": "RAW MATERIAL SUPPLY",
          "description": "This module takes into account the extraction and processing of all raw materials and energy which occur upstream to the studied manufacturing process."
        },
        {
          "module": "A2",
          "number": null,
          "title": "TRANSPORT TO THE MANUFACTURER",
          "description": "The raw materials are transported to the manufacturing site."
        },
        {
          "module": "A3",
          "number": null,
          "title": "MANUFACTURING",
          "description": "This module takes into account the production process."
        },
        {
          "module": "A4",
          "number": null,
          "title": "TRANSPORT TO THE BUILDING SITE",
          "description": "Fuel type and consumption of vehicle or vehicle type used for transport: Truck 16-32 ton EURO 5 (0,260 l/km), Truck >32 ton EURO 5 (0,366 l/km), Truck 7.5-16 ton EURO 5 (0,186 l/km)\n\nDistance: 100 km (40% from factory to construction site), 35 km (60%*85% from supplier to construction site), 100 km (60% from factory to supplier), 35 km (60%*15% from supplier to construction site)\n\nCapacity utilisation (including empty returns): 50%\n\nBulk density of transported products: Ecoinvent\n\nVolume capacity utilisation factor: Ecoinvent\n\nThe B-PCR provides default transport scenarios for the transport to the building site for cases where specific data on transport are missing. The B-PCR provides scenario's for this life cycle stage. Fibre cement panels are categorized as 'loose products' in table 5 of the B-PCR. The following transport steps apply:\n• 40% directly to the construction site over 100 km with a 16-32 ton lorry (ecoinvent record: 'Transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U')\n• 60% to a supplier over 100 km with a >32 ton lorry (ecoinvent record: 'Transport, freight, lorry >32 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry >32 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U')\n• 85% of these 60% is transported over 35 km from supplier to construction site with a 16-32 ton lorry (ecoinvent record: 'Transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U')\n• 15% of these 60% is transported over 35 km from supplier to construction site with a 7.5-16 ton lorry (ecoinvent record: 'Transport, freight, lorry 7.5-16 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry 7.5-16 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U')"
        },
        {
          "module": "A5",
          "number": null,
          "title": "INSTALLATION IN THE BUILDING",
          "description": "12,5 inox screws are necessary per functional unit for Cedral lap and 10 inox clips are necessary for Cedral clip. In this EPD an average has been considered by including 50% of the screws (6,25 screws or 0,019 kg) and 50% of the clips (5 clips or 0,060 kg). For the installation of 1m² CEDRAL product, 0.022 kWh of electricity is declared. The dataset used to model the impacts is 'Electricity, low voltage {BE}| market for | Cut-off, U'.\n\nDuring the installation, depending on how the CEDRAL sheets are cut, there is a loss rate between 5-30%, depending on the building shape. For this EPD an average loss rate of 10% is used. All packaging material for the CEDRAL product is transported to End of Life (EoL) and disposed of in line with the B-PCR default EoL scenarios for Belgium.\n\nParts of the installation:\n- Processes necessary for the installation of the product: 0,022 kWh energy needed to fix the screws\n- Fixation materials: 6,25 Screws, 5 Clips\n- Material losses: 10% Average material losses\n- Packaging: Pallet 0,6787 kg, PE cover foil 0,0041 kg, PE plastic foam layers 0,1545 kg, PE band on a carton roll 0,1620 kg\n- Ancillary materials for installation (specified by material): 12,5 Screws, 10 clips\n- Water use: None\n- Other resource use: 10% losses\n- Quantitative description of energy type (regional mix) and consumption during the installation process: 0,022 kWh electricity, low voltage\n- Waste materials on the building site before waste processing, generated by the product's installation (specified by type): packaging waste: 0,6787 kg wood, packaging waste: 0,321 kg plastic\n- Output materials (specified by type) as result of waste processing at the building site e.g. of collection for recycling, for energy recovery, disposal (specified by route): 60% recycling, 20% incinerated (wood); 35% recycling, 60% incinerated, 5% landfill (plastic)\n- Direct emissions to ambient air, soil and water: None\n- Distance: Not applicable"
        },
        {
          "module": "B1",
          "number": null,
          "title": "USE STAGE - Use",
          "description": "No emissions during the use phase."
        },
        {
          "module": "B2",
          "number": null,
          "title": "USE STAGE - Maintenance",
          "description": "The product does not require maintenance."
        },
        {
          "module": "B3",
          "number": null,
          "title": "USE STAGE - Repair",
          "description": "The product does not require repair."
        },
        {
          "module": "B4",
          "number": null,
          "title": "USE STAGE - Replacement",
          "description": "No replacement required."
        },
        {
          "module": "B5",
          "number": null,
          "title": "USE STAGE - Refurbishment",
          "description": "No refurbishment"
        },
        {
          "module": "B6",
          "number": null,
          "title": "USE STAGE - Operational energy use",
          "description": "The product does not require operational energy use."
        },
        {
          "module": "B7",
          "number": null,
          "title": "USE STAGE - Operational water use",
          "description": "No operational water use."
        },
        {
          "module": "C1",
          "number": null,
          "title": "END OF LIFE - Deconstruction/Demolition",
          "description": "The dismantling of EQUITONE [tectiva] involves the same amount of energy as for the installation, which is 0,022 kWh."
        },
        {
          "module": "C2",
          "number": null,
          "title": "END OF LIFE - Transport to waste processing",
          "description": "The default scenario for fibre cement boards from NBN/DTD B08-001 describes that the end-of-life waste is transported to a sorting facility over a distance of 30 km. Afterwards, 100% of the fibre cement boards and 5% of the metal screws and clips are transported to a landfill over a distance of 50 km.\n\nModule C2 – Transport to waste processing:\nType of vehicle: Truck 16-32 ton\nFuel consumption: 0,260 l diesel/km\nDistance (km): 80\nCapacity utilisation (%): 50%\nDensity of products (kg/m³): Ecoinvent scenario\nAssumptions: Ecoinvent scenario"
        },
        {
          "module": "C3",
          "number": null,
          "title": "END OF LIFE - Waste processing for reuse, recovery and/or recycling",
          "description": "No recycling/reuse of fibre cement boards, 95% recycling of metal screws\n\nEnd-of-life modules – C3 and C4:\nWastes collected separately: 0,079 kg\nWastes collected as mixed construction waste: 19,5 kg\nWaste for re-use: 0 kg\nWaste for recycling: 0,075 kg\nWaste for energy recovery: 0 kg\nWaste for final disposal: 19,5 kg"
        },
        {
          "module": "C4",
          "number": null,
          "title": "END OF LIFE - Disposal",
          "description": "100% landfill of fibre cement boards, 5% landfill of metal screws\n\nEnd-of-life modules – C3 and C4:\nWastes collected separately: 0,079 kg\nWastes collected as mixed construction waste: 19,5 kg\nWaste for re-use: 0 kg\nWaste for recycling: 0,075 kg\nWaste for energy recovery: 0 kg\nWaste for final disposal: 19,5 kg"
        },
        {
          "module": "D",
          "number": null,
          "title": "BENEFITS AND LOADS BEYOND THE SYSTEM BOUNDARIES",
          "description": "In module D, the benefits and loads beyond the system boundaries are quantified. Following waste streams are considered after their end-of-waste: wooden pallets in A3 and A5 (of which 60% is recycled), plastic packaging in A3 and A5 (of which 35% is recycled), paper and cardboard in A3 (of which 95% is recycled), steel cables in A3 (of which 95% is recycled) and metal screws and clips (of which 95% is recycled).\n\nQuantitative description of the loads beyond the system boundaries:\n- Treatment of 0,078 kg of scrap steel to prepare it for to prepare it for recycling at the remelter\n- Sorting of 0,408 kg of waste wood to prepare it for recycling\n- Treatment of 0,113 kg plastic to prepare it for recycling\n\nQuantitative description of the benefits beyond the system boundaries:\n- Avoided production of 2,40 MJ of heat using natural gas\n- Avoided production of 1,20 MJ of Belgian electricity mix\n- Avoided production of 0,078 kg primary steel\n- Avoided production of 0,408 kg primary softwood\n- Avoided production of 0,113 kg primary polypropylene/ polypropylene granulates"
        }
      ]
    },
